snippet.textDisplay: Great work, the control arms (specially the rubber bearings) should be fastened while the car is standing on the ground or lifted axle. The rubber bearings can worn out very quickly if they not installed correctly. Use new oil change screw (includes the seal ring) and torque them with Audi spec torque. Otherwise you can kill the oilpan or the leak is not fix.

I'll do few things different way:
I know is difficult on the drive way but always tightened arms bolts when car is in "drive" position on wheels, so you won't rip off bushes to quick. Always properly clean wheel hub b4 installing brake disc, you'll avoid discs vibrations. Always do bleading from the farthest point from brake pump.

snippet.textDisplay: Tightening arm bolts should be made under weight of vehicle on level ground to set origin for bushes correctly. In this case 0 stress position for bushes would be at fully rebounded suspension. Think what happens with rubber when it is twisted and quite large forces are applied...
